From 832973fdb212c7ff4fcf41d9c7375d56aa43c7b2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Emergent E1 <e1@emergent.dev>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 16:48:52 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(team): refresh UI with tabs, modal-based edit,
 radar-inside DETECT, high-contrast theme

- Team header is now compact: name + level chip + pencil (opens Edit modal)
- Team attributes (name/Context/Level/Purpose) moved into modal, freeing the page
- Tab switcher between Radar and Strategies (with counts)
- 'Detect' button relocated to the right of 'Radar / Environmental view'
- Env changes are now editable: detail modal has Edit button opening prefilled form (PUT /environmental-changes/:id)
- Radar shows small labels next to each point (auto-anchored outward, 24-char truncation)
- Modern high-contrast dark theme: layered background/card/tile surfaces
- Distinct section accents: cyan (team) / violet (strategy) / amber (changes)
- Level accepts values >= 0 (preserves existing behavior)
